# Tests for {{MODULE_NAME}} Module

Terratest-based integration tests for the {{MODULE_NAME}} Terraform module.

## Prerequisites

- Go 1.21 or higher
- AWS credentials configured
- Terraform installed

## Running Tests

### All Tests

```bash
go test -v -timeout 30m
```

### Specific Test

```bash
go test -v -run Test{{MODULE_NAME_UNDERSCORED}}Module -timeout 30m
```

### Parallel Tests

```bash
go test -v -parallel 3 -timeout 60m
```

## Test Structure

- `basic_test.go` - Basic functionality tests
- Tests use Terratest to deploy real infrastructure
- Resources are automatically cleaned up after tests

## Development

### Adding New Tests

1. Create new test function: `func TestMyFeature(t *testing.T)`
2. Use `t.Parallel()` for parallel execution
3. Configure terraform options
4. Use `defer terraform.Destroy()` for cleanup
5. Add assertions with `assert` package

### Test Best Practices

- Always clean up resources (use defer)
- Use parallel execution when possible
- Set appropriate timeouts
- Test one feature per test function
- Use descriptive test names

## Cost Optimization

- Tests create real AWS resources (costs money)
- Use smallest instance types for testing
- Clean up is automatic (via defer)
- Run only necessary tests during development
